[White "The Caveman Accepted: Mainline"]
[Black "3. The Caveman Mainline: 8... Qxa1 and 11... Qe5"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h5 5. Bg5 Qb6 6. Bd3 Bxd3 7. Qxd3 Qxb2 8. e6
Qxa1 9. Qb3 Qxd4 10. Qxb7 fxe6 11. Be3 Qe5 12. Nf3
{ Winning a tempo on Black's queen. } 12... Qd6 13. Qxa8
{ It's finally time for White to cash in. } 13... Nf6 14. Bxa7 Nd7 15. Qb7
{ An important move. White prevents Black from playing ...Qc7, and threatens Qc8+. }
15... Kf7 16. O-O Kg8 17. Ng5 Rh6
{ Notice the miserable position of the f8-bishop. If Black tries to improve this piece with  17...g6  , however ,  18.Qc8 !  followed by Qe8 is decisive. }
18. Nd2 Rf6 19. Rb1
{ Black can't do anything about the threat of Bxb8 winning a piece. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "The Caveman Accepted: Mainline"]
[Black "4. The Caveman Mainline: 8... Qxa1 and 11... Qe5, 15... c5"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h5 5. Bg5 Qb6 6. Bd3 Bxd3 7. Qxd3 Qxb2 8. e6
Qxa1 9. Qb3 Qxd4 10. Qxb7 fxe6 11. Be3 Qe5 12. Nf3
{ Winning a tempo on Black's queen. } 12... Qd6 13. Qxa8
{ It's finally time for White to cash in. } 13... Nf6 14. Bxa7 Nd7 15. Qb7 c5
16. Qc8+
{ A second theme in the Caveman mainline is the weakened light squares on Black's kingside. Here White makes maximum use of them! }
16... Kf7 17. Ng5+ Kg8 18. Qe8 { Threatening Qf7 mate. } 18... Rh6
{ This prevents the mate, but allows a neat combination.   18...Qe5+  19.Kf1  Qf4   19...Rh6  20.Qf7+  Kh8  21.Qxf8+!  is similar to the text  20.g3!  and Black's queen has to let go of either the b8-knight or the f7-square. }
19. Qf7+ Kh8 20. Qxf8+ Nxf8 21. Nf7+ Kg8 22. Nxd6 exd6 23. Bxb8
{ White has won a piece. } *

