[Black "5. The Caveman Mainline: 8... Qxa1 and 11... Qc4"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h5 5. Bg5 Qb6 6. Bd3 Bxd3 7. Qxd3 Qxb2 8. e6
Qxa1 9. Qb3 Qxd4 10. Qxb7 fxe6 11. Be3 Qc4 12. Nf3
{ The a8-rook won't run away, and now White has the deadly threat of Ne5. }
12... Nd7
{ Relatively best is  12...Qa6  13.Qxa8  Qc8  , but after  14.Bxa7  White again simply wins the b8-knight. }
13. Qxa8+ Kf7 14. Ng5+ Kf6 { 14...Kg6  15.Qe8+  is similar. } 15. Qe8
{ With the deadly threat of Qf7+. } 15... Kf5
{ Ashwin - Kasparova went  15...Qb4+  16.Nd2  1-0. } 16. Qxd7
{ White is a piece up and has a winning attack. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "The Caveman Accepted: Mainline"]
[Black "6. The Caveman Mainline: 8... Qxa1 and 9... b5"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h5 5. Bg5 Qb6 6. Bd3 Bxd3 7. Qxd3 Qxb2 8. e6
Qxa1 9. Qb3 b5 10. Nf3
{ Now that Qxb7 is no longer a threat, White switches course and aims to trap the a1-queen. Nf3 protects the d4-pawn so Black's queen has no moves, and also prepares O-O. }
10... a5 { This doesn't work out.  10...Nf6  instead transposes to line 8. }
11. O-O
{ White calmly continues developing. He is already threatening Nbd2 and Nc3. }
11... a4 12. Qa3 fxe6
{ 12...b4  13.Qxb4  Qxa2  allows Black's queen out of her prison , but after  14.Qb7  Black is already being mated:  14...fxe6  15.Qc8+  Kf7  16.Ne5#. }
13. Nc3 Qxf1+ 14. Kxf1
{ Materially, Black now has two rooks and two pawns for the queen. However he has a ton of weaknesses, his king is not exactly safe, and he has no good way to solve his development problems. }
14... Nd7 15. Ne2 { Going to f4. } 15... Ngf6 16. Nf4 Kf7 17. Ne5+
{ There are a lot of promising alternatives as well. } 17... Nxe5 18. dxe5 Ng4
{ 18...Ne4  19.Qh3!  targeting e6.   18...Nd7  19.Qh3! } 19. Qd3 Kg8 20. Qg6
Nxe5 21. Qxe6+ Nf7 22. Ng6 Rh7 23. Qxc6
{ White will pick up all the pawns on the queenside after which he has an easy win. }
