{ Retreating with  9.Bd2  would be insipid. White must develop as fast as possible! }
9... fxg5 10. O-O gxh4 11. Nbd2
{ Finishing development and threatening to trap Black's queen with Rfb1. }
11... Qb6 12. Rfb1 Qa6 13. Qg6+ Kd8 14. Ne5 Nh6 15. c4
{ Also strong is  15.Qxh5  with an initiative  (Goeller)  (.)  Notice how all of Black's pieces - apart from the queen - are doing absolutely nothing at all! }
