{ What else? Notice how almost all of Black's pieces are locked in. } 16. Ndxc4
Kc7 17. Rc1 { White calmly piles up on the c-file. } 17... Ng4 18. d5 Nxe5
{ 18...cxd5  19.Nb6+!  Kxb6  20.Rab1+  Ka5  21.Qc2  leads to mate. } 19. Nxe5
Qe2 { 19...Rh6  20.Qe8!  would not improve Black's position. } 20. dxc6
{ Also good is  20.d6+  Kxd6  21.Nf7+  and White picks up the h8-rook. } 20...
Nxc6
{ 20...b6  21.Rd1!  Qxe5  22.Qe8!  and White has a decisive attack.   20...Qxe5  21.cxb7+  Kxb7  22.Rab1+  Ka6  23.Qd3+  Ka5  24.Qa3# }
21. Nxc6 bxc6 22. Qf5 { Threatening Qa5+. } 22... Qa6 23. Qe5+ Kd8 24. Qd4+
{ White's queen enters on d7 and mate follows. } *

