16... Nb6 { 16...Nf6  17.Bf4+  Ka8  18.Na4!  with a decisive attack. } 17. Bf4+
Ka8 18. Qa5 { Pinning the b6-knight and re-introducing the idea of Na4. } 18...
Re8 19. Nd4
{ White is threatening to put a knight on b5. Mate can hardly be prevented. } *

