[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h5 5. Bg5 Qb6 6. Bd3 Qxd4 7. Nf3 Qg4 8. Bxf5
Qxf5 9. c4 Qe4+ 10. Be3 e6 11. Nbd2 Bb4 12. O-O Bxd2 13. Qxd2 Qxc4 14. Rac1
Qxa2
{ This line demonstrates some resources for White if Black grabs the a2-pawn. }
15. Ra1 Qc4
{ 15...Qb3 ?  16.Nd4 !  and Black is in trouble. He has to resort to  16...Qb6   16...Qc4 ?  17.Rfc1  traps the queen.  17.Nxe6  c5  and here both Nxc5 and Nxg7+ are very promising for White. }
16. b3 Qg4 { 16...Qxb3 ?  17.Rfb1  Qc4  18.Rb4  -+ } 17. Ra4 Qg6 18. Qb4
{ White's queen decisively penetrates the queenside. } 18... b6 19. Qd6
{ White is already threatening moves like Bxb6 and Rxa7. } *

