[White "The Caveman Accepted: 6... Qxd4"]
[Black "42. The Caveman 6... Qxd4: 7... Qg4, 9... Qe4+ and 14... Qa6"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h5 5. Bg5 Qb6 6. Bd3 Qxd4 7. Nf3 Qg4 8. Bxf5
Qxf5 9. c4 Qe4+ 10. Be3 e6 11. Nbd2 Bb4 12. O-O Bxd2 13. Qxd2 Qxc4 14. Rac1 Qa6
{ This is another alternative. Now Black's queen guards b7, but the kingside is less well defended now. White can play on the dark squares: }
15. Bc5 Nd7 16. Qg5
{ Black now has several moves, including ...Rh6, ...Qd3 and ...g6, and in each case White can answer 17. Bd6 with good compensation. In any case Black should not play }
16... Nxc5 17. Qxg7 { White wins material. } *

