[White "The Caveman Declined: Mainline"]
[Black "48. The Caveman Declined: 8... Qa6"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h5 5. Bg5 Qb6 6. Bd3 Bxd3 7. Qxd3 e6 8. Nd2
Qa6 9. c4
{ Perhaps someone can grind out a win in the endgame after  9.Qxa6  Nxa6  , but that's not the Caveman style. }
9... Bb4 { Threatening ...Qxc4. } 10. b3 Ne7 11. Ne2 Nd7 12. O-O Bxd2
{ 12...O-O?  13.a3  Bxd2  14.Bxe7  is good for White. } 13. Qxd2 Nf5
{ Black cannot castle until he moves the e7-knight away.   13...dxc4  14.Bxe7  Kxe7  15.Ng3!  Kf8  16.Ne4  and White has excellent compensation for the pawn. }
14. cxd5 cxd5 15. Ng3 { Eliminating a defending piece on the kingside. } 15...
Nxg3 { 15...g6?!  16.Nxf5  gxf5  17.Qb4!   15...Ne7  16.Bxe7  Kxe7  16.Qg5+ }
16. fxg3 O-O 17. Bf6 { This leads to a winning attack. } 17... gxf6 18. exf6
Rfc8 19. Qh6 Nxf6 20. Qg5+ Kf8 21. Qxf6
{ Black resigned in Lahno - Khotenashvili  (Tbilisi 2011)   because of  21...Rc7  22.Qh8+. }
*

