[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h5 5. Bg5 Qb6 6. Bd3 Bxd3 7. Qxd3 e6 8. Nd2
Qa6 9. c4 Bb4 10. b3 c5 11. Nf3
{ Here, since Black has played ...c5, having the knight on f3 gives White extra resources involving dxc5  (with the knight on e2 Black could answer that move with Nxe5)  . }
11... Nc6 12. O-O Nge7 13. dxc5 Bxc5 14. a3 { Threatening b4. } 14... dxc4 15.
Nxc4
{ White is still threatening b4-b5, since Qxb5 will be answered by Nd6+ picking up the queen. }
15... Rd8 16. Qc2 O-O 17. b4 Bd4 18. Rad1
{ Black has to be careful that he isn't squeezed away! } *

