1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h5 5. Bg5 Qb6 6. Bd3 Bxd3 7. Qxd3 e6 8. Nd2
c5 9. c4 { White cannot allow Black the possibility of ...c4. } 9... Nc6 10.
Ngf3 cxd4 11. cxd5 Nb4
{ 11...exd5  12.O-O  is better for White. If Black does not watch out, White will play e6! fxe6 Qg6+. }
12. Qb3 Nxd5 13. Qa4+
{ This is the issue with 10... cxd4 - now Black has to enter a slightly worse ending. }
13... Qc6 14. Qxc6+ bxc6 15. Nxd4
{ White has a small endgame advantage based on the better pawn structure. } *

