{ This move provides White with a lot more headaches than the crude 10...Qxd4. With ...Nc6 Black increases his pressure on d4 such that   11.cxd5  Qxd4!  doesn't seem to lead to much -  12.Qb3   or  12.Qb5  Qb4!  Qxe5+  13.Ne2  Nd4!.  Therefore, White should probably bolster d4 and continue developing with 11. Ngf3 but this in turn allows Black's knight to go to b4 and then either to c2 with check or take on a2, after which Black threatens ...Nc3 with a fork on Rd1 and Qe2. }
