1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h6 5. g4 Bh7 6. e6 Qd6 7. exf7+ Kxf7 8. f4
Nf6 { The standard move. } 9. Nf3
{ White is more or less forced to sacrifice the g4-pawn. Other moves would allow Qe6+ followed by Nxg4 anyway. }
9... Nxg4 10. h5
{ This clamps down on the g6-square and prevents Black from playing ...h5 himself, which would help him significantly. }
10... Nd7 11. Nc3 e6 12. Ne5+ Ngxe5 13. fxe5 Nxe5
{ White has to be careful in how to answer this piece sacrifice. } 14. Bf4
