[Black "98. The Botvinnik-Carls Gambit: 4... Nc6, 5... Bf5 and 6... Nxe5"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. Ne2 Nc6 5. c3 Bf5 6. dxc5 Nxe5
{ Instead of first playing ...e6 Black can also directly take this pawn. It delays his development but allows more flexibility with his light-squared bishop. }
7. Nd4 Bd7
{ 7...Bg6?  not only weakens the a4-e8 diagonal , but also allows  8.f4!  Nd7  9.f5  and Black can hardly avoid losing a piece. }
8. b4
